  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7001.22 sitting right on the massive 7000 gamma wall (20.7B), dealers are actively selling into this strength to hedge their long gamma position, creating immediate resistance. The PIN regime with GEX flip at 6860 means dealers will continue providing liquidity against the move - selling rallies toward 7025/7050 and buying any dips back toward 6860. Key levels to watch: 7000 as immediate resistance where selling pressure intensifies, and 6860 as the critical support where dealer buying would accelerate on any breakdown.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect the market to get pinned around 7000 with dealers capping upside moves.",
